#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.special.elliprj.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.special.elliprj"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:1 of
msgid "Symmetric elliptic integral of the third kind."
msgstr "第三类对称椭圆积分。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:3 of
msgid "The function RJ is defined as [1]_"
msgstr "函数 RJ 定义为 [1]_"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:5 of
msgid ""
"R_{\\mathrm{J}}(x, y, z, p) =\n"
"   \\frac{3}{2} \\int_0^{+\\infty} [(t + x) (t + y) (t + z)]^{-1/2}\n"
"   (t + p)^{-1} dt"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:12 of
msgid ""
"This function should be considered experimental when the inputs are "
"unbalanced.  Check correctness with another independent implementation."
msgstr "当输入不平衡时，此函数应被视为实验性。请使用另一个独立实现检查正确性。"

#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.special.elliprj.rst
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:15
#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:20
#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:25
#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:30 of
msgid ""
"Real or complex input parameters. `x`, `y`, or `z` are numbers in the "
"complex plane cut along the negative real axis (subject to further "
"constraints, see Notes), and at most one of them can be zero. `p` must be"
" non-zero."
msgstr ""
"实数或复数输入参数。`x`、`y` 或 `z` 是复平面上沿负实轴切割的数字（受"
"进一步约束，参见注释），其中至多有一个为零。`p` 必须非零。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:35 of
msgid "Optional output array for the function values"
msgstr "函数值的可选输出数组"

#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.special.elliprj.rst
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:38 of
msgid ""
"**R** -- Value of the integral. If all of `x`, `y`, `z`, and `p` are "
"real, the return value is real. Otherwise, the return value is complex.  "
"If `p` is real and negative, while `x`, `y`, and `z` are real, non-"
"negative, and at most one of them is zero, the Cauchy principal value is "
"returned. [1]_ [2]_"
msgstr ""
"**R** -- 积分值。如果 `x`、`y`、`z` 和 `p` 都是实数，则返回值为实数。否则"
"，返回值为复数。如果 `p` 是实数且为负数，而 `x`、`y` 和 `z` 是实数、非"
"负数，且其中最多一个为零，则返回柯西主值。[1]_ [2]_"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:38 of
msgid ""
"**R** -- Value of the integral. If all of `x`, `y`, `z`, and `p` are "
"real, the return value is real. Otherwise, the return value is complex."
msgstr ""
"**R** -- 积分的值。如果 `x`、`y`、`z` 和 `p` 都是实数，则返回值为实数。"
"否则，返回值为复数。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:41 of
msgid ""
"If `p` is real and negative, while `x`, `y`, and `z` are real, non-"
"negative, and at most one of them is zero, the Cauchy principal value is "
"returned. [1]_ [2]_"
msgstr ""
"如果 `p` 为实数且为负数，而 `x`、`y` 和 `z` 为实数、非负数且最多有一个为"
"零，则返回柯西主值。[1]_ [2]_"

#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.special.elliprj.rst
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:48 of
msgid ":py:obj:`elliprc`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:49 of
msgid "Degenerate symmetric integral."
msgstr "退化的对称积分。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:51 of
msgid ":py:obj:`elliprd`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:52 of
msgid "Symmetric elliptic integral of the second kind."
msgstr "第二类对称椭圆积分。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:54 of
msgid ":py:obj:`elliprf`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:55 of
msgid "Completely-symmetric elliptic integral of the first kind."
msgstr "第一类完全对称椭圆积分。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:57 of
msgid ":py:obj:`elliprg`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:58 of
msgid "Completely-symmetric elliptic integral of the second kind."
msgstr "第二类完全对称椭圆积分。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:61 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:62 of
msgid ""
"The code implements Carlson's algorithm based on the duplication theorems"
" and series expansion up to the 7th order. [3]_ The algorithm is slightly"
" different from its earlier incarnation as it appears in [1]_, in that "
"the call to `elliprc` (or ``atan``/``atanh``, see [4]_) is no longer "
"needed in the inner loop. Asymptotic approximations are used where "
"arguments differ widely in the order of magnitude. [5]_"
msgstr ""
"代码实现了基于倍增定理和级数展开至七阶的 Carlson 算法。[3]_ 该算法与其在 "
"[1]_ 中的早期形式略有不同，因为在内循环中不再需要调用 `elliprc`（或 ``"
"atan``/``atanh``，见 [4]_）。当参数在数量级上差异很大时使用渐近近似。[5]_"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:69 of
msgid ""
"The input values are subject to certain sufficient but not necessary "
"constraints when input arguments are complex. Notably, ``x``, ``y``, and "
"``z`` must have non-negative real parts, unless two of them are non-"
"negative and complex-conjugates to each other while the other is a real "
"non-negative number. [1]_ If the inputs do not satisfy the sufficient "
"condition described in Ref. [1]_ they are rejected outright with the "
"output set to NaN."
msgstr ""
"当输入参数为复数时，输入值需满足某些充分但非必要的约束。特别地，``x``、``"
"y`` 和 ``z`` 必须具有非负实部，除非其中两个为非负数且互为复共轭，而另一个"
"为实数非负数。[1]_ 如果输入不满足参考文献 [1]_ 中描述的充分条件，则直接"
"拒绝输入并将输出设为 NaN。"

#: maxframe.tensor.special.ellip_func_integrals.elliprj:77 of
msgid ""
"In the case where one of ``x``, ``y``, and ``z`` is equal to ``p``, the "
"function ``elliprd`` should be preferred because of its less restrictive "
"domain."
msgstr ""
"当 ``x``、``y`` 和 ``z`` 中有一个等于 ``p`` 时，应优先使用函数 ``elliprd`"
"`，因为其定义域限制较少。"

